name: Thom Astro
summary: Thom Astro is a French science influencer known primarily for his educational science content on social media, engaging a broad audience with accessible explanations of scientific concepts[10]. He has built a strong reputation for clear communication and reliability in science outreach, often appearing on lists of top science influencers in France[10].

name: Yassine Sdiri
summary: Yassine Sdiri is a French tech entrepreneur and one of the leading francophone influencers in artificial intelligence, best known as the founder of ChatflowAI and for his widely followed YouTube channel dedicated to making AI accessible to businesses and entrepreneurs[1][3][4]. He enjoys a strong reputation for his practical, educational content and expertise in AI, with tens of thousands of followers, making him a respected figure among tech professionals and startup communities in France[1][3].

name: Hugoposé
summary: **Hugoposé** (born Hugo, formerly HugoPOSAY or MultiGaming01) is a French gaming and entertainment YouTuber recognized for his humorous videos and lively engagement with a fanbase of nearly 5 million subscribers as of July 2025[1]. He is respected for blending gaming content with comedic sketches and interactive series, earning a strong reputation for community involvement and a thoughtful approach to content creation[1][3].

name: PLK
summary: PLK is a French rapper, born Mathieu Pruski in Paris in 1997, known for his Polish and Corsican heritage and his early start in hip-hop as a member of Panama Bende before launching a highly successful solo career[1][3][5][15]. He is widely recognized in France for his authentic lyrics, impressive flow, and sustained commercial success, with multiple gold and platinum records, millions of albums sold, and a strong reputation as a leading figure in modern French rap[1][3][5].

name: Scilabus
summary: Scilabus is a French science education channel on YouTube created by Viviane Lalande, known for making scientific topics accessible and engaging for the general public, including beginner learners[1][2]. The channel has a strong reputation for clear, approachable explanations and is recognized as one of the leading French science education influencers, praised for its ability to simplify complex issues and boost scientific curiosity[1][4].

name: Christopher Michaut
summary: Christopher Michaut, known online as **Mr. Bacchus**, is a French art influencer and digital curator recognized for his creative artistic stagings and collaborations with prestigious institutions like the Louvre and the Kunsthistorisches Museum of Vienna[1][3][8]. He has built a strong reputation for making art accessible and engaging to a broad audience through visually striking content and educational mediation, amassing over 51,000 Instagram followers as of 2025[1][3][5].

name: Dimitri Monique

name: Ninho
summary: Ninho, born William Nzobazola, is a French rapper of Congolese descent acclaimed for his versatility, impactful lyrics, and pioneering presence in French hip hop and trap music[1][3][5][7][11]. He enjoys a strong reputation as one of France’s most influential rappers, holding the record for the highest number of certified singles and earning praise for his authentic depiction of life in French suburbs and numerous high-profile collaborations[1][11].

name: Céline Dion
summary: Céline Dion is a **world-renowned Canadian singer** known for her powerful vocals and hit songs in both French and English, including the Oscar-winning "My Heart Will Go On" and "Beauty and the Beast"[1][3][5]. She enjoys a reputation as one of the most successful and awarded pop vocalists in history, celebrated for her technical skill and emotional performances[3][7][9].

name: Gotaga
summary: **Gotaga**, whose real name is Corentin Houssein, is a highly successful French gaming influencer, streamer, and professional esports player best known for his expertise in the Call of Duty franchise[1][10][11]. He enjoys an acclaimed reputation as "The French Monster," widely recognized as the most prominent French console player, with large audiences across Twitch and YouTube and international renown within competitive gaming[1][3][7][10][11].

name: Bodytime
summary: **Bodytime** is a French fitness brand co-created by Pierre-Jean Cabrieres, known for offering online training programs and exercise wear and amassing a large social media following[1][5][11]. The brand and its founders have a strong reputation for clarity in their fitness guidance and are recognized among the leading French fitness influencers and YouTubers[13].

name: Squeezie
summary: **Squeezie**, born Lucas Hauchard, is a highly influential French gaming YouTuber and streamer, widely recognized as the most prominent French-speaking gamer with over 18 million subscribers and billions of views[3][5][9][11]. He is known for his comedic gaming content and vlogs, earning a reputation as a superstar in France and the first influencer honored with a statue at the Grévin Museum[1][5].

name: Leadorablee (Léa)
summary: Leadorablee (Léa) is a French travel influencer known for sharing inspiring travel experiences, photography, and lifestyle content across Instagram and her blog since 2013, with a focus on wide open spaces and beautiful landscapes rooted in her Val d'Isère origins[1][3][7]. Léa enjoys a strong reputation for authenticity and adventure, has visited over 50 countries, and engages a dedicated following of over 150,000 on Instagram, making her a respected voice in the French travel community[1][5][11].

name: Juju Fitcats
summary: **Juju Fitcats** (Justine Becattini) is a leading French fitness influencer and content creator renowned for her humorous, body-positive, and diverse posts about fitness, nutrition, and lifestyle[1][2][5][7]. She has built a strong reputation for promoting self-confidence, making fitness enjoyable, and actively engaging her millions of followers through interactive challenges and relatable everyday content[1][3][5][7].

name: Garance Doré
summary: **Garance Doré** is a French illustrator, writer, and photographer widely recognized as one of the original fashion influencers, who rose to fame with her blog and candid approach to style and storytelling[1][3][11]. She is respected for her authentic voice, artistic talent, and for shaping modern online fashion culture, earning a reputation as an authoritative and enduring figure in the world of French style and art[1][2][11].

name: Lila Bonbon
summary: Lila Bonbon is a French beauty influencer recognized for her vibrant TikTok makeup tutorials and personal reflections on beauty trends, self-empowerment, and community support[1]. She enjoys a strong reputation for relatable, heartfelt content and active engagement with her audience, establishing herself as a prominent figure in the beauty and lifestyle niche[1].

name: Maeva Ghennam
summary: Maeva Ghennam is a French reality television personality and social media influencer, best known for her appearances on "Les Marseillais" and for her significant online following[1][5][7][3]. She is known for her glamorous lifestyle and has attracted both popularity and controversy, with her reputation sometimes questioned due to issues of credibility, cosmetic surgery, and frequent media attention[2][9].

name: Bon Pote
summary: **Bon Pote** is an independent French media platform founded in 2020 by Thomas Wagner, a former banker turned climate influencer, which focuses on science communication about climate change and environmental issues[1]. It enjoys a strong reputation for producing well-documented, accessible articles often cited as references, though it also faces criticism for its activist tone and media status, sparking debates within the ecological community[1].

name: Les Recettes de Juliette
summary: "Les Recettes de Juliette" is a French culinary influencer known for sharing healthy, vegetarian, and seasonal recipes through her blog and social media platforms. She has built a reputation for promoting eco-friendly cooking and simple, accessible recipes, making her a popular figure among those interested in green and wholesome cuisine.

name: Instanonimal
summary: Instanonimal is a **French tech influencer** known for sharing tips on the latest technology trends, product recommendations, and coverage of major international tech events[3]. He is regarded as **one of the most renowned tech influencers in France**, with a reputation for delivering comprehensive and informative content to his followers[3].

name: Léo Duff
summary: **Léo Duff** is a French tech influencer and YouTuber known for his in-depth, accessible analyses of innovation and technology, with a particular focus on the Apple ecosystem[1][3][7]. He enjoys a reputation for **constructive, well-argued critiques and a strong educational approach**, making him a respected voice among both enthusiasts and the broader public[2][6][7].

name: It’s so Paris
summary: It’s so Paris is a French travel influencer on Instagram with 375,000 followers, recognized for sharing content about travel experiences in and around Paris[1]. Their account is regarded as a notable presence among French travel influencers, indicating a positive reputation and significant influence in the travel community[1].

name: Dirty Biology
summary: **Dirty Biology** is the online pseudonym of Léo Grasset, a French science communicator and YouTuber renowned for his humorous and creative approach to biology and popular science, whose channel has over 1.2 million subscribers[1][5]. While highly influential in French science communication, his reputation has been marred since 2022 by multiple public allegations of sexual harassment and sexism, leading to demonetization of his channel and loss of sponsors[1][2].

name: Michou
summary: Michou, whose real name is Miguel Mattioli, is a French gaming YouTuber and influencer known for his engaging and humorous content, especially on games like Clash Royale and Fortnite, amassing over 10 million subscribers on YouTube[1][3][5]. He enjoys a strong reputation as one of France's top digital creators, recognized for his positive energy, authentic approach, and broad influence across the gaming and entertainment communities[3][14].

name: Marie Lopez
summary: **Marie Lopez**, known online as **EnjoyPhoenix**, is a prominent French **lifestyle influencer, YouTuber, and entrepreneur** renowned for her content on fashion, beauty, and personal advice[1][3][5][7][9][11][12][13]. name: Esra (lilyslilah)
summary: Esra, known online as **Lilyslilah**, is a French-Turkish beauty influencer recognized for her engaging content on makeup, fashion, and lifestyle across platforms like TikTok, Instagram, and YouTube[1][3][5]. She has built a strong and positive reputation for her authenticity, creativity, and high-profile brand collaborations, earning her a top position among French beauty influencers[1][3].

name: ArtBen
summary: **ArtBen** is a French tech influencer recognized for his engagement in the European technology scene, notably highlighted at events such as Viva Technology[2]. He is known for his expertise and opinion leadership in tech innovations, earning international exposure and a positive reputation among media and corporate partners[2].

name: Tibo InShape
summary: Tibo InShape, whose real name is Thibaud Delapart, is a French fitness influencer and YouTuber known for his bodybuilding content and humor, with over 26 million subscribers and a reputation as one of the most prominent French-speaking creators[1][5][7]. While he is widely recognized for his positive impact in popularizing fitness and social media trends, he has also faced controversy over resurfaced online posts accused of racism and homophobia[1][7].

name: Nota Bene
summary: **Nota Bene**, real name Benjamin Brillaud, is a French educational YouTuber and author renowned for his accessible and engaging videos on history and mythology, with over 2.5 million subscribers as of 2024[3][5][9][11]. He has a strong reputation in the Francophone world for the quality and accuracy of his historical content, making complex subjects approachable to a broad audience[5][7][11].

name: Diegsalbin
summary: Diegsalbin is a French travel influencer with approximately 186,000 followers, known for sharing travel and lifestyle content through engaging social media posts[2]. They have established a solid reputation within the French travel influencer community by ranking among the top Instagram travel profiles in France, reflecting both popularity and credibility in the travel niche[2].

name: SDM
summary: **SDM**, real name Beni Mosabu, is a French rapper of Congolese descent born in 1995 who rose to prominence after signing with Booba's label 92i and is recognized as a leading figure in the new generation of French rap[1][5][9]. He is known for his commercial success, notably with the track "Bolide allemand"—the most streamed song in France in 2023—and has a strong reputation as one of the most popular and influential artists in the French hip-hop scene[1][9].

name: Werenoi
summary: **Werenoi** (Jérémy Bana Owona) was a French rapper and songwriter, widely recognized for his authentic style and for being France’s top-selling music artist with chart-topping albums in 2023 and 2024[1][5][3]. Celebrated for his powerful lyrics and significant influence on the French hip-hop scene, he earned critical acclaim and a devoted following before his untimely death in 2025 at age 31[3][11].

name: Sardoche
summary: Sardoche, whose real name is Andréas Honnet, is a prominent French Twitch streamer and former professional League of Legends player known for his competitive gaming skills and large online following[3][7][10]. His reputation is marked by both significant achievements—such as winning PogChamps 3—and controversy, including several Twitch bans and a widely recognized polarizing presence in the French gaming community[3][4][5][2].

name: FastGoodCuisine
summary: **FastGoodCuisine** is the online alias of Charles Gilles-Compagnon, a French web videographer, author, and entrepreneur renowned for his accessible cooking content and the most-followed French-language culinary YouTube channel, boasting over 6 million subscribers[3][5]. He is highly regarded for popularizing easy, inventive recipes and has earned accolades such as the ForYouAwards, cementing his reputation as a leading influencer in the French culinary scene[3][4][6].

name: Domingo
summary: Domingo, whose real name is Pierre-Alexis Bizot, is a prominent French streamer and esports commentator best known for his gaming content—especially around League of Legends—and for hosting popular events and shows on Twitch[1][3][13]. He enjoys a strong reputation in the French streaming community, recognized for his engaging personality, versatility in content, and his successful transition from competitive gaming to large-scale entertainment and digital media production[1][3].

name: Kameto
summary: Kameto, whose real name is Kamel Kebir, is a prominent French gaming influencer and Twitch streamer with over 2 million followers, best known as the co-founder and CEO of the major European esports organization Karmine Corp[1][5][7]. He is highly regarded for both his entrepreneurial success in esports—including leading Karmine Corp to multiple championships—and his influential, authentic connection with the French gaming community[1][13].

name: Sananas
summary: **Sananas** (real name Sanaa El Mahalli) is a prominent French beauty and lifestyle influencer known for her highly popular YouTube and Instagram content focused on makeup, fashion, and skincare, with over 3 million subscribers and frequent collaborations with luxury brands[1][3][5][7][8]. She is respected for her expertise and engaging style but has also faced some reputation challenges related to transparency in sponsored content, which she has publicly addressed[1].

name: Monsieur Phi
summary: **Monsieur Phi** is the pseudonym of Thibaut Giraud, a French philosopher, writer, and former philosophy teacher, known for his educational YouTube channel focused on philosophical popularization, which has over 387,000 subscribers[1][3][7]. He is recognized for his rigorous and accessible approach, with his content recommended by the French Ministry of Culture for its educational value and reputation for critical inquiry[1].

name: Herve Cuisine
summary: **Hervé Cuisine** is the online pseudonym of Hervé Palmieri, a French chef, bestselling author, and creator of the popular Hervé Cuisine YouTube channel and blog dedicated to approachable, delicious home cooking since 2007[3][6][7]. He is widely respected for his accessible video recipes, large online following (over 940,000 followers on Instagram), and positive reputation as a leading French food influencer and cookbook author[3][7].

name: Prashant Kirad
summary: Prashant Kirad is an Indian educator, entrepreneur, and motivational speaker who is the CEO of ExpHub, an education technology platform, and co-founder of Next Toppers, known for his simplified teaching approach in Physics and Chemistry for JEE and NEET aspirants.[1][3] With millions of subscribers across multiple YouTube channels and a reputation built on authentic, trust-based teaching rather than commercial production, he has become one of India's top education influencers, having mentored over 100,000 students and earned the affectionate title "Prashant Bhaiya" from his community.[1][3][5]

name: Manon Laime
summary: Manon Laime is a French digital creator and Instagram influencer based in Paris, known for her fashion, lifestyle, and travel content, and has amassed over 230,000 followers on her account[1][3]. She is recognized for her aesthetic style and has developed a reputation for authenticity, notably working with brands like Eau Thermale Avène as a trusted partner in long-term campaigns[1][5].

name: Léo Techmaker
summary: **Léo Techmaker** (real name Léo Locurcio) is a prominent French tech influencer and digital creator known for educational content on platforms like YouTube and Instagram, where he has gathered a large following by simplifying complex technology topics and showcasing new high-tech gadgets[1][3][5][7]. He is widely respected in the French tech community for making technology accessible, engaging, and fun to a broad audience through clear explanations and hands-on demonstrations[5][7].

name: Justine Gallice
summary: Justine Gallice is a French fitness entrepreneur, digital creator, and co-founder of the fitness app Fiit Fight Forever, recognized for her accessible workout routines and positive approach to health and well-being[1][2][4]. She has built a strong reputation as one of France's most influential fitness personalities, widely respected for promoting body positivity, sustainable fitness, and motivating a large social media community through her professional and empathetic content[1][2][3][4].

name: Pierre | Prof de Maths
summary: Pierre, known as "Prof de Maths" on social media, is a French influencer who creates educational content focusing on mathematics, with references to sports themes, and has gained recognition for his engaging teaching style. He is respected online for making math approachable and enjoyable, particularly among young French audiences interested in both academics and sports[17].

name: Les Revues du Monde
summary: **Les Revues du Monde** is a French educational YouTube channel created and presented by Charlie Danger, specializing in accessible history and archaeology content since 2014[12][7][9]. The channel is highly regarded in France for its rigorous approach to debunking misinformation and is the country's second-most-followed historical vulgarization channel, praised for making complex subjects engaging and relevant[2][5][11].

name: Voyages Pirates
summary: **Voyages Pirates** is a widely recognized French travel influencer platform specializing in curating affordable travel deals and tips for francophone audiences[1]. Their reputation centers on providing reliable, budget-focused travel information, earning them significant popularity among French travelers seeking inspiration and practical guidance[1].

name: SCH
summary: **SCH** is a French rapper and songwriter, born Julien Schwarzer in Marseille in 1993, widely recognized for his unique voice, cinematic storytelling, and influential blend of trap and noir-inspired hip hop[1][3][7][13]. He is regarded as a leading figure in French rap, respected for his artistic depth and commercial success, with a reputation for both underground credibility and mainstream appeal[1][11].

name: Gims
summary: **Gims** is a French-Congolese singer, rapper, producer, and songwriter, best known for his solo career and as a former member of the prominent hip-hop group Sexion d'Assaut[1][3][5][9]. He enjoys a reputation as one of France’s most successful urban music artists, celebrated for his versatile blend of hip-hop, pop, and Afrobeat, multiple platinum albums, and authentic style[1][9].
